ABUJA – Federal Government said it has completed 23 water supply projects and nine dams since the inception of the present administration. Engr. Suleiman Adamu, Minister of Water Resources, disclosed this at the just concluded four-day top management retreat organised by the Ministry in Uyo, Akwa Ibom State. Adamu explained that on assumption of office in 2015, he inherited 41 uncompleted water supply projects, and 37 dams, adding that 13 water supply projects had been completed and commissioned, while additional 10 water projects had been completed and awaiting commissioning. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The minister expressed his desire to finalise and implement the Flood Management Master Plan for River Niger and Benue as well as aggressively implement the Water and Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) programme and end open defecation by 2025. Other priority areas, according to him, included, support the implementation of water management and water settlement project in the National Livestock Transformation Plan (NLTP). He reiterated the determination of his ministry to partner with private sector to create massive jobs for the teeming Nigerian youths. The retreat was used to consider and review score cards of all technical departments and agencies of the ministry against set benchmark of the Water Resources Roadmap 2016-2030. Earlier, Mrs. Ekaro Comfort charged the participants to pay adequate attention to the retreat and contribute significantly to the achievements of the ministry’s agenda.